<h2>Slide and Stack Glass Walls</h2>
Looking for custom exterior doors for either your business or home? Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup> finally has the perfect solution in our Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls. Comprise these operable walls of individual panels which slide along a top hung track and stack to a remote location. The Slide &amp; Stack System is designed to accommodate many panels, and typically ranges in sizes over 48" wide. While the wall is open, the panels stack into a parking bay. Panel parking bays can be parallel or perpendicular to the track, feature multiple bays, exist at one or both ends of the wall, or stack into a pocketed area. In addition, custom bays can be designed to make the most out of any project's spacial constraints. Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls are top hung systems requiring headers to bear the weight of the unit. Any engineering questions can be discussed furthermore with Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup>' in-house engineering team.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignleft wp-image-36864 size-full" title="slide &amp; stack glass walls" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Stack-Desc.png" alt="slide &amp; stack glass walls" width="896" height="584" />[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1502913840172{padding-top: 50px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-36877 size-full" title="slide &amp; stack glass walls" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Stack-Res.png" alt="slide &amp; stack glass walls" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>Residential Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls</h2>
The unique configurations and ease of operation of Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls make them ideal for custom residential applications. They are also used as exterior walls of a home which open up entirely, including corners and segmented radius walls. Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls are also used as residential pool &amp; spa enclosures or as a custom pool house. The wide range of panel parking options including pockets therefore, making it incredibly easy incorporating them into any home.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]
<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-36876 size-full" title="slide &amp; stack glass walls" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Stack-Comm.png" alt="slide &amp; stack glass walls" width="896" height="488" /></h2>
<h2>Commercial Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls</h2>
Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls are extremely versatile and are frequently used in restaurants, storefronts, offices, hotels, and educational facilities. Their ability to round corners, span unlimiting expanses, and move completely out of sight when open make Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls ideal for office &amp; hotel conference rooms and other multi-use spaces. Use Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls for storefronts or exterior facades that completely remove indoor/outdoor barriers during the day but lock up securely after hours.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36820 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/thermal-break-icon-small-1.png" alt="" width="150" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Thermally Enhanced</h2>
The thermal break separates the aluminum and minimizes conductivity of heat and cold from the inside to the outside to ensure a structureâ€™s interior remains comfortable at any time of year.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36899 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/engineering-icon.png" alt="Custom Engineering for Custom Glazed Windows and Doors" width="120" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Custom Engineered</h2>
Each Solar Innovations systemÂ is custom made to order based on your project needs and preferences. Our team of engineering experts has you covered.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36822 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Ease-of-Operation-icon-small-1.png" alt="" width="69" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Ease of Operation</h2>
Solar Innovations' systems offer single-handed operation and move smoothly with little effort. Much of our hardware is manufactured in house which allows us to control lead times.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-36827 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/monster-sizes-icon-small.png" alt="" width="62" height="102" /></h2>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">Monstrous Sizes</h2>
Solar Innovations has the ability to manufacture even larger panels that operate with greater ease for several functions: folding, sliding, swinging, and stacking.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignleft wp-image-36870 size-full" title="slide &amp; stack glass walls" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Stack-Track.png" alt="slide &amp; stack glass walls" width="896" height="488" />[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="3/4"][vc_column_text]
<h2></h2>
<h2>Trackless Options</h2>
Install our Slide &amp; Stack Systems without a floor track for a completely seamless transition between two spaces. After closing, our two point locking handles secure the concealed rods into discrete individual dust proof floor strikes. Our trackless option is especially useful for conference room dividers and other flexible multipurpose environments where an wider floor space is desired when open.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=".vc_custom_1502972276540{padding-top: 50px !important;}"][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignnone wp-image-36895 size-full" title="slide &amp; stack glass walls" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Stack-Finish-1.png" alt="slide &amp; stack glass walls" width="896" height="488" />
<h2>Frames &amp; Finishes</h2>
Use Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup>' Slide &amp; Stack Glass WallsÂ as either interior or exterior walls with thermal or non-thermal rail options. Thermally-enhanced frames contain insulbar, which creates a barrier preventing temperature transfer year round. Use non-thermal frames for interior systems, in applications with limited weather exposure, or rather those regions with minimal weather fluctuation. A wide range of standard, designer, and custom finishes are available, including wood clad &amp; veneer options.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignnone wp-image-36893 size-full" title="slide &amp; stack glass walls" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Stack-Config-1.png" alt="slide &amp; stack glass walls" width="896" height="488" />
<h2>Configurations</h2>
Utilize Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls for straight, angular, multiple face, and curved openings. Design units in a 60 degree, twin trolley configuration. Locate the dual trolleys above the vertical rails of the glass panels allowing them to slide with greater ease along the track, and the 60 degree design of the panel parking bay allows for one hand operation of the stacking panels. Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup> also designs and engineers custom trolley and stacking configurations. Finally, install these systems with Solar or with one of our nationwide dealers.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignnone wp-image-36896 size-full" title="slide &amp; stack glass walls" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Stack-Glazing.png" alt="slide &amp; stack glass walls" width="896" height="488" />
<h2>Glazing Options</h2>
Solar InnovationsÂ® Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls can incorporate any glazing option available on the market today. Utilize Low-e glazing for both residential and commercial applications because it helps maintain a comfortable indoor temperature, reduces energy consumption, and provides protection from UV rays. Custom decorative glass options are also available to create a unique look or match an existing project. The glass can be tinted, acid etched, frosted, art glass, or contain applied grids (available with multiple pattern options).[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]<img class="alignleft wp-image-36917 size-full" title="slide &amp; stack glass walls" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Stack-Operation-300.gif" alt="slide &amp; stack glass walls" width="300" height="271" />
<h2>Operation</h2>
The Slide &amp; Stack System operates as individual top hung panels which slide along a track and stack to a remote location. After closing panels, they are secured in place with the turn of a handle, bolting the panels into both the track above and the sill below. In our standard 60 degree panel stacking bay configurations, the panels can typically operate while using a single hand.

See our video playlist for full demonstrations of the operation of Slide &amp; Stack Glass Walls.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]<code>[video_lightbox_youtube video_id="ELgyAGpIdvo" width="679" height="403" anchor="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/Stack-Video.png"  alt="slide and stack glass walls"]</code>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_tabs style="flat" shape="square" active_section="1"][vc_tta_section i_icon_fontawesome="fa fa-info-circle" add_icon="true" title="Product Overview" tab_id="1469019690642-0abf0dea-3861"][vc_column_text]<a href="https://solarinnovations.com/downloads/SI3000S Stacking Glass Wall Cut Sheet.pdf"><img class="alignright wp-image-25556 size-full" src="https://solarinnovations.com/wp-content/uploads/coverpage1.png" alt="coverpage1" width="400" height="248" /></a>The Series SI3000S top hung thermally enhanced aluminum stacking glass walls are suitable for use in commercial and residential applications. Multiple sill options and profile dimensions provide greater performance and design flexibility. Customization of product profiles, hardware, sills, and testing can be completed.

Multiple sill options and profile dimensions provide greater performance and design flexibility. Customization of product profiles, hardware, sills, panel size, and testing can be completed upon request.
